1. COMPLETED — Restock requests and individual restock items can now be placed on hold from the Purchase Orders workflow, managed from a dedicated Purchase Orders > On Hold section, and released only when linked back to an open PO.

Implementation details:
- Added a database migration, `supabase/migrations/20260514020000_add_restock_hold_workflow.sql`, that extends `restock_requests.status` with `on_hold`, makes `restock_items.restock_request_id` nullable so an individual held item can be intentionally orphaned from its original request, adds hold metadata fields (`held_from_request_id`, `hold_status`, `held_at`, `held_by`, `hold_notes`), adds foreign keys for original-request and held-by tracking, and adds indexes for hold-status and held-request lookup performance.
- Updated restock TypeScript types so request statuses include `on_hold` and restock items can represent active lines, request-held lines, or orphaned held lines with their hold metadata.
- Added server actions for the complete hold lifecycle:
  - `putRestockRequestOnHold` marks an entire request `on_hold`, clears any PO link, marks all its items `hold_status = 'on_hold'`, and writes restock history.
  - `putRestockItemOnHold` moves one item to hold, nulls `restock_request_id` to intentionally orphan it, stores the original request in `held_from_request_id`, recalculates the original request total, and writes restock history.
  - `getHeldRestockItems` loads orphaned held items for the PO tab.
  - `releaseHeldRestockRequestToPurchaseOrder` requires an open PO for the same supplier, links every held item into that PO, restores item `hold_status = 'active'`, and moves the request to `linked_to_po`.
  - `releaseHeldRestockItemToPurchaseOrder` requires an open PO for the held item supplier, creates a new system-generated restock request, attaches the orphaned item to that new request, links the item to the selected PO, and writes restock history.
- Updated the restock workflow UI so the Purchase Orders tab has an `On Hold` status section beside Open, Placed, Received, and Cancelled. This section displays both whole requests on hold and orphaned held items.
- Added request-level hold controls in request detail modals for eligible requested requests.
- Added item-level hold controls in request detail modals for eligible requested items.
- Added a release-from-hold modal that forces staff to select an open manual or scheduled PO for the same supplier before a request or orphaned item can leave hold.
- When a held orphaned item is released, the UI/action path creates and links a new system-generated request, preserving the existing application structure rather than attaching a PO item without a request.
- Existing PO creation continues to link only active `requested` restock requests; held items and held requests remain excluded until explicitly released from hold.

How to verify this task was truthfully completed:
1. Apply the Supabase migrations, then confirm the schema has:
   - `restock_requests.status` check constraint containing `on_hold`.
   - nullable `restock_items.restock_request_id`.
   - `restock_items.hold_status`, `held_from_request_id`, `held_at`, `held_by`, and `hold_notes` columns.
2. Start the admin app and open `/admin/restock`.
3. Create or locate a requested restock request with at least two items and no linked PO.
4. Open the request from Current Requests, click `Hold item` for one line, then open Purchase Orders > On Hold. Verify:
   - The held line appears as a held item.
   - The original request still exists with the held line removed from its active total.
   - The held item has `restock_request_id = null`, `held_from_request_id` set to the original request, and `hold_status = 'on_hold'` in the database.
5. Create or locate an open PO for the same supplier, click `Create request and link to PO` for the held item, select that PO, and submit. Verify:
   - A new `restock_requests` row was generated with an `RR-*` request number, status `linked_to_po`, and `purchase_order_id` set to the selected PO.
   - The held item now has `restock_request_id` equal to that new request, `hold_status = 'active'`, and `purchase_order_item_id` set.
   - The selected PO has the released item as a PO line or merged into a matching existing line.
6. Create or locate another requested restock request and click `Put Request On Hold`. Verify:
   - The request leaves Current Requests and appears in Purchase Orders > On Hold.
   - The request status is `on_hold` in the database.
   - Its items have `hold_status = 'on_hold'` but remain attached to the same request.
7. Create or locate an open PO for the same supplier, click `Link to PO` on the held request, select the PO, and submit. Verify:
   - The request status becomes `linked_to_po`.
   - `purchase_order_id` is set to the selected PO.
   - All request items return to `hold_status = 'active'` and have `purchase_order_item_id` values.
8. Attempt to release a held request or held item when no open same-supplier PO exists. Verify the release modal has no valid PO to select, enforcing the requirement that leaving hold must link to a PO.
9. Run `npx tsc --noEmit` and verify TypeScript passes.
10. Run `npm run lint` and verify lint passes.
